<h3><a name="cancel">I've moved... how do I cancel my reminder?</a></h3> 
 
<p>When you sign up for Recollect we send you an email that contains instructions on how to cancel the service.  Also, each time you are billed we send you an invoice with instructions on how to cancel the service.</p> 
 
<p>Please note that if you cancel your service we do not offer any refunds.</p> 
 
<h3><a name="data">Where does the data come from? Is this official?</a></h3> 
 
<p>The geo-data about the zones comes from your city's website. We tend to focus on cities that have open data portals and that share this information freely with the public.</p> 
 
<p>The schedule data is copied from the City's official schedule.  It is our goal to ensure that this data is always up to date and correct.  If you ever believe you are getting a reminder on the wrong day, please notify us.</p>

<h3><a name="mycity">How can I get garbage reminders for my City?</a></h2> 
 
<p>Contact us! We are presently in the process of rolling out Recollect across more and more cities, if you'd like us to roll out to your city let us know! If you city already shares garbage zone and schedule information in an open data portal we'd definitely like to know.</p> 

<p>If you <i>don't</i> have open data for garbage zones in your city, then more work is required. If you want to help to build Recollect for your city, we require two datasets to import the city.  The first is the geographic data that describes the polygons for each zone, in KML format.  The second is a CSV file of the schedule.  The CSV format is <code>zone-name,yyyy-mm-dd,GR</code>. The third column describes what is picked up that day - G=garbage, R=recycling, Y=yard compost, 2G = Two garbage bin pickup, F=food bank pickups, X=xmas tree.
 
<h3><a name="publicofficial">I'm a Mayor, Councillor, Public Official or Solid Waste contractor, how do I get Recollect in my community?</a></h3> 
 
<p>We'd love to talk to you. We currently have a roll out strategy for major cities in Canada and the United States but are looking for city partners interested in bringing Recollect to their city. We believe our extremely low cost service can improve customer service, reduce waste and create a valuable way to inform users of service changes. Please check out our <a href="/partner">Partner Page</a> to learn more and/or <mailto:partner@recollect.net>email us</a> to set up an appointment.</p> 
 
